cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with join algorithms for indexed search trees, which are commonly used in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely category. The paper also introduces a new notion of complexity called certificate complexity, which extends previous work on data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely category. The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to optimize the join algorithm, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
